// This file is a placeholder. Unity scene files (.unity) are binary YAML
// and must be created from within the Unity Editor.
//
// To create the AnankeDemo scene:
//
//   1. Open this project in Unity 6.
//   2. Create a new scene: File > New Scene > Basic (Built-in).
//   3. Add an empty GameObject named "AnankeController".
//   4. Add the Ananke/AnankeController component to it.
//   5. Create two capsule GameObjects: "Entity1" (position 0,0,0) and
//      "Entity2" (position 0.6,0,0) to represent the two combatants.
//   6. Assign Entity1 and Entity2 to the "Entity Objects" array in the
//      AnankeController Inspector.
//   7. Save the scene as Assets/Ananke/AnankeDemo.unity.
//
// The sidecar must be running before you press Play:
//   cd sidecar && npm start
